<br>
&quot;Abashi: The fastest horses will rival a Bard running song.&quot;<br>
<br>
WTF is up with this? Fastest speed rivals Bard Song / spirit of cheetah? Ok surely you drop off the horse when you attack then right? Think again.<br>
<br>
&quot;From horseback all forms of combat and casting can be performed.  Bard Song, Spirit of Wolf, etc will not stack with the horse's running speed&quot;<br>
<br>
This is insanity. Soloing will now become a completely trivial matter to those with enough plat. Could you imagine a necro or wizard on the back of one of these? If they allow you to meditate while riding one consider it the end of EQ as we know it. A smart caster would be completely immune to any form of retribution on horseback. Its not just casters either. A smart ranger can now bow kite his way to victory without even breaking a sweat. Bard speed is very very fast, especially at lvl 60. But on to one of the real issues, PvP.<br>
<br>
Its obvious they have completely given up on PvP. Anyone on the fastest horse will completely own you, period. Even if you can pummice/golem wand it off it is an instant click item (at least by all initial reports). Throw in the new rediculous &quot;alternative advancements&quot; like a lure based root and mana burn and your basically looking at an end to meaningful PvP. You thought the melee range bug was bad before? Wait until some caster is trying to gank you moving at Bard speed. This is an uterly stupid idea and one that should never have left the stables.<br>
<br>
If this doesn't piss bards off it should. Verant constantly told us that they wouldn't make horses that would come close to going as fast as a bard. It was a lie. Some crackhead at Verant decided they needed a massive money sink so they made the big horses cost 100,000+pp. Guess what genius? You could have made the fastest horse rival a shaman sow speed of your level and just as many people would have bought it. Man, sometimes the stupidy that goes on just pisses me off. I had to vent my steam, and I know its a game and all but I was hoping beyond all hope they wouldn't go and do something stupid like this.<br>
<br>
Pickk <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upickkpockket999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pickk Pockket999</A> at: 12/4/01 5:48:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/01 6:20:58 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~shadowcross/clip.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Horse Speeds</span><hr size=1> You can't cast while RIDING, although you can cast while on HORSEBACK.<br>
